  {
    "user": "U02E4DAQGSZ",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1765139501.587609",
    "client_msg_id": "0a64e5f6-2841-4d4a-8634-2b910ecf1f93",
    "text": "There is a missing semantic in Dataflow programming, something like function calling but not exactly that. After many attempts, I think I finally nailed it: Dataflow Templating. While I have got it working for Observable Dataflow, I think this equally applies to its forefathers like <https://docs.racket-lang.org/frtime/|FrTime>. I could reexplain it here but its in the article. I saw <@U06BUK2M2RH> grappling with the same thing for <https://feelingofcomputing.slack.com/archives/C5T9GPWFL/p1764186658018769|Artifact>. I don't use diagrammatic representations of dataflow, but if I did, I would be trying to figure out what the graphical representation of this is.\n\n<https://observablehq.com/@tomlarkworthy/dataflow-templating>",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
