        "fallback": "Observable: Dynamic Dataflow Templating",
        "text": "The missing function-like semantic for dataflow programming. Why? There is a reusability gap with notebooks (and spreadsheets for that matter). When you express a complex chain of computation, they build upon a set of initial inputs, unrolled across a series of cells. But then you realize, there is no way you can reuse the same logic with different inputs. But I love dataflow, notebooks, inspectable cells and the accompanying documentation! The inspectability of intermediate steps with dataflow programming",
